The paper deals with compressed sensing, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves sparsity promoting regularization, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses numerical experiments, which suggests that it may fall under numerical analysis (cs.NA). The use of regularization and optimization techniques in image processing is also mentioned, which could place it under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a Bayesian information criterion, which is a statistical method, suggesting it may also fall under statistics (cs.SI).
